//@version=4
study("basics/type_as_identifier_v4")
// `type` only became a keyword in v5, so a v4 script may use it as an ordinary
// name — including as a function parameter, which is how it shows up in the wild.
//
// v4 has no `log.*` namespace — bare `log` is math's natural logarithm — so this
// fixture can't print. It asserts the v4 spelling parses and runs.
_label(type) => "ESD:" + type

type = "EARNINGS"
tag = _label(type)

// Expected output:
